Doctors Without Borders (MSF) nurse Bhelekazi Mdlalose prepares herself to perform a swab test for COVID-19 coronavirus on health workers at the Vlakfontein Clinic in Lenasia. JOHANNESBURG - The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases increased by 1,218, the health department reported. Ten new deaths have also been recorded, taking the toll to 407. The latest number of infections soared to 21,343. READ: South Africa's COVID-19 cases surpass 20,000 mark Gauteng, the Eastern Cape and Western Cape recorded the highest new cases in the past 24 hours. The Western Cape is still the epicentre with the country's highest death toll, now standing at 261. So far, 564,370 tests have been conducted. Recoveries stand at 10,104. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.